Microssa

Class Order

  • java.lang.Object
    • Microssa.Order

  • public class Order
extends java.lang.Object
    Object used to store order details. An order is a willingness to buy or sell (Side) some amount (Quantity) of a real or virtual object (Symbol) for a specific dollar amount (Price). Other fields serve as identifiers or special instructions for the order.

      • ArriveDate

        private java.lang.String ArriveDate
        The date this Order arrived. Currently unused.

      • TIF

        private java.lang.String TIF
        The Time in Force of the order. Valid values are DAY meaning the order will sit in the book until either fully filled or the matching engine is shut down, or IOC (Immediate or cancel) meaning the Order will immediately match but, if not fully filled, will expire rather than sit in the book waiting for subsequent matches.

      • Price

        private double Price
        The price the Order would like to buy or sell. Actual match prices may be better depending on market conditions, meaning lower than a buy Order's price or higher than a sell Order's price.

      • Quantity

        private double Quantity
        The maximum amount of goods to buy or sell.

      • AvailableQuantity

        private double AvailableQuantity
        The remaining quantity on the order. Would be less than Quantity if the order was partially filled, or zero if the order was fully filled.

      • Side

        private char Side
        Whether this is a buy or sell Order.

      • SettlementDate

        private java.lang.String SettlementDate
        The day the order will settle.

      • Currency

        The currency of the order.

        Minimum fill quantity for a partial execution.
